text: Teague Barn Wabash Importing Company Farm Stable, also known as the Miller Barn, is a historic bank barn located in Noble Township, Wabash County, Indiana. Its original section was built in 1861, and is a three-story, post- and-beam frame barn on a limestone foundation. It measures 40 feet by 80 feet and features a paneled frieze and soffit, sunburst gable vent, and chamfered support posts.
